00:42:17.679 --> 00:42:22.179
I mean, we can all name cases,
but in general,

00:42:22.179 --> 00:42:29.282
the engineers who create
devices are forced out of top

00:42:29.282 --> 00:42:37.460
management and replaced by
people who are general managers.

00:42:37.460 --> 00:42:43.143
That's what happened at
Polaroid, but it happened too

00:42:43.143 --> 00:42:43.909
late.
 

00:42:43.909 --> 00:42:46.949
It happened much too late.
 

00:42:46.949 --> 00:42:50.500
Now if you were going to save
Polaroid,

00:42:50.500 --> 00:42:55.338
let's say in the 1980s,
let's suppose you are Mack

00:42:55.338 --> 00:43:01.559
Booth and it's your task to give
this company the best chance of

00:43:01.559 --> 00:43:06.300
preserving its value going into
the future,

00:43:06.300 --> 00:43:07.659
what would you do?
 

00:43:07.659 --> 00:43:11.804
What they did do was a hell of
a lot of R&amp;D on a long

00:43:11.804 --> 00:43:14.320
